\frac{\sqrt{x^2+1}}{x^4} = \frac{\sqrt{1+\frac1{x^2}}}{x^3} = \frac1{x^3} \cdot \sqrt{1+\frac1{x^2}}.
t=\frac1x
\newcommand{\dd}{\; \mathrm{d}}\int \frac1{x^3} \cdot \sqrt{1+\frac1{x^2}} \dd x =  \begin{vmatrix} x=\frac1t & \dd x = -\frac{\dd t}{t^2} \\ t=\frac1x & \dd t = -\frac{\dd x}{x^2}\end{vmatrix} =  -\int t\sqrt{1+t^2} \dd t.
